Furry Visual Novel Game Jam 2025

Platform:
Gameboy/Color Gameboy

Optional Theme: 
Retro (should be nailing it with the gameboy and 90's IRC aesthetic)

Engine/Software used:
Custom GBZ80 engine, using RGBDS assembler
Aseprite - Art
NEXXT - Art
hUGETracker - Music

Schedule:
12 days total (ends Dec. 1st 9am AEDT)
Days 1-4: Engine design and testing
Days 5-8: MVP: Getting basic VN laid down with at least placeholder art and sounds
Days 8-11: Iterating: adding more stuff from the feature list as needed, working on the mechanics, tweaking anything needed
Day 12: Final Polish
Day 12: Submission Day

Basic Concept:
A shortform horror VN about the protag discovering more than they should on an IRC, intended to be played for between 5-15 minutes (may be longer if things go well)

Elevator Pitch:
Set in the 90's in a suburban area, the player, their first weekend home alone in a while decides to research local legends by joining a cryptid IRC chat room and finds that the legends may be closer to home than anticipated, presented in a short form horror VN format

Art Style:
A realistic art style, depicting real life locations crunched down to 160*144@2bpp, attempting to breed familiarity in the player to relatable locations


Overview of features required for VN engine:
Scene loading from cartridge
ROM banking (need to research mapper carts)
Dialogue parsing and rendering
Resizable text boxes
Character rendering onto screen (maybe using OAM's? Max size is 48*48 if OAM based, OAM's would make transitions easier)
Dialogue choice's/menu dialogs
 ^needs to be affected by previous choices (have flags definable)
String storage for later (8 characters?)
Parsing string replacements in dialogue renderer (check for $name____ and replace with name strvar as needed)
Reversed palette text rendering with a flag
Scene transitions
Actor transitions
Sound effects playing
Music playing
Using DMA to copy data to speed it up for animations/loading (needs a HRAM handling function)

Gameplay loop example:
Transition from off
Display image of main menu
Press Start
Transition to an intro background
Play Dialogue
Ask for name, store name
Play more dialogue
Transition to a second background
Transition to show actor
Dialogue
Actor change state (from greeting to talking)
Dialogue
Actor change state (from talking to worried)
Dialogue
Transition to hide actor
...ETC...

General Engine Loop:
Globally owned:
    Music Handler
    Sound Handler
    Metasprite
    Story Flag Array
    Scene pointer

Main
Ticks scene pointer that's stored
    Scene (Scene owns the game loop)
        Actor (owns the loop during transitions)
        Dialogue (owns the loop when rendering out text)

Scene contents:
Data included in a bank that has space
have an initialise function where the background gets loaded

Immediate To-do:
