*Research and implement MBC5 mapping
*Test MBC5 mapping by placing a test image on a different bank and rendering it
Come up with a scene format that will work
*Test loading 6*6 metaobjects and moving them around to see how DMG handles that much data
Try flipping through animations with it (animation handler needed)
Implement a test scene without the correct formatting to ensure basic engine works
Slowly move the aboves entire setup into the decided format
Transitions that consist of either fading in/out (backgrounds) or sliding in/out from left/right (OAMs)
Research a scanline interrupt at the top of the dialogue box for rendering text using objects

Friday to-do:
Upgrade the text renderer to allow any size of text box via X/Y position instead of address
Two test scenes, one big test scene and a small one
Test Actors made in Aseprite ready to use as a template
Test backgrounds made in Aseprite ready for template usage
Metasprite Handlers (disable: sets the position way out of frame, sets all tiles to 0. destination move: used for transitions)


Needed for MVP:
Basic storyboard done
House layout done
Design bible finished
